<set-var title="strip-tags: Meta-HTML Utility">
<include header.mhtml>

<layout::page>
  <h3> Remove HTML and <meta-html> Tags from Input </h3>
  <ptext>
    <synopsis strip-tags [filename...]>

    <code>strip-tags</code> removes all HTML and <meta-html> tags from its
    input stream, and produces an output stream of what remains.  If 
    <var filename> arguments are given, <code>strip-tags</code> reads
    from those input files, and creates a new output file for each one
    called <code><var filename>-stripped</code>.  Otherwise, strip-tags
    reads from the standard-input and writes to the standard-output.

    This is a very useful utility when creating indices for a search
    engine.
  </ptext>
</layout::page>
